    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Proposal for Giuliani</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Robert S Gruber says if Mayor Rudolph W Giuliani really wants to reach out to family of Patrick Dorismond (May 22 article) he could give graduation address at public schools in minority areas next month</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mayor Says He Wants to Reach Out to Dorismond Family'' (news article, May 22):</p>
        <p>Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani is to be commended for his desire ''to break down the barriers that I've created.'' Initially, he could concentrate on race relations and public education.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mayor Says He Wants to Reach Out to Dorismond Family'' (news article, May 22):</p>
        <p>Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani is to be commended for his desire ''to break down the barriers that I've created.'' Initially, he could concentrate on race relations and public education.</p>
        <p>I suggest that, health permitting, he give the graduation address at a number of elementary, junior high and high schools in minority areas next month.</p>
        <p>ROBERT S. GRUBER  New York, May 23, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a former public high school teacher.</p>
      </block>
